Combine light corn syrup, butter and sugar in saucepan; simmer until syrup-like. Pour mixture over the bottom of a 9"x 13" pan. Slice bread into 12-16 slices; place over the syrup. Layer as needed. Beat together the eggs, milk, vanilla, and salt. Pour over bread. Cover with saran wrap. Refrigerate overnight. Bake in a preheated oven 350 degree F (175 degrees C) for 45 minutes. Cut into squares. Invert and serve.